Nepal Earthquake Disaster Email Scams (Alert)   In the aftermath of the devastating earthquake in Nepal, just like major disasters before it, human nature is often at its best, but for some, it is at its worst. Following major disasters, scammers usually send out floods of email in an attempt to either solicit donations for fake charities, or else to lure users into clicking links containing malware or responding to phishing attempts. New York, Accra, Madrid & Tel Aviv   NYU community members in New York, Accra, Madrid, and  Tel Aviv can contact the IT Service Desk in a number of ways:    For help by telephone , call 1-212-998-3333 to speak with IT Service Desk staff 24 hours a day, seven days a week. (NYU-NY community members can simply call 8-3333 from on-campus phones.)    For help online , submit your question (including as many details as possible) using the contact form or by sending email to AskITS@nyu.edu . A representative will respond to the email address you supply within one business day.    For in-person help in New York , visit the IT Service Desk at 10 Astor Place, 4th floor, from Monday through Friday, 9am to 6pm ET. For help with configuring your laptop computer, however, call 1-212-998-3333 first to make an appointment. Nepal Earthquake Disaster Email Scams (Alert)   In the aftermath of the devastating earthquake in Nepal, just like major disasters before it, human nature is often at its best, but for some, it is at its worst. Following major disasters, scammers usually send out floods of email in an attempt to either solicit donations for fake charities, or else to lure users into clicking links containing malware or responding to phishing attempts. For self-service support and request forms for services provided by ITS and an ever-expanding number of other NYU-provided services, explore NYU ServiceLink .       New York, Accra, Madrid & Tel Aviv   NYU community members in New York, Accra, Madrid, and  Tel Aviv can contact the IT Service Desk in a number of ways:    For help by telephone , call 1-212-998-3333 to speak with IT Service Desk staff 24 hours a day, seven days a week. (NYU-NY community members can simply call 8-3333 from on-campus phones.)    For help online , submit your question (including as many details as possible) using the contact form or by sending email to AskITS@nyu.edu . A representative will respond to the email address you supply within one business day.    For in-person help in New York , visit the IT Service Desk at 10 Astor Place, 4th floor, from Monday through Friday, 9am to 6pm ET. For help with configuring your laptop computer, however, call 1-212-998-3333 first to make an appointment.     Abu Dhabi   NYU community members at NYU Abu Dhabi can contact the IT Service Desk 24 hours a day, seven days a week by sending email to nyuad.it.help@nyu.edu or by calling 971-2-628-8888 (or simply 8-8888 from on-campus phones).   NYU Abu Dhabi Campus Technology Center walk-in hours on the 3rd floor of the Library are: Sunday-Thursday, 8am-7pm GST; Friday: closed; Saturday: 12pm-7pm GST.   Berlin   NYU community members at NYU Berlin can contact the IT Service Desk by sending email to AskITS@nyu.edu or by calling 49-30-290291-333 (or simply 333 from on-campus phones).
